el unless the result also meets one of the policy cases\\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:434:### FS-human-intervention-resolution: Human intervention resolution\\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:436:Items that carry `human-intervention` must not depend on per-item manual triage\\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:440:This resolution is currently automated by Rhei. The `human-intervention-scanner`\\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:441:workspace template periodically scans the open `human-intervention` queue —\\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:455:§FS-human-intervention-policy.\\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:458:zero dynamic-access calls are never human-intervention on their own, because the\\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:476:following must not be escalated to `human-intervention` or a requested-changes\\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:477:review on coverage-depth grounds (§FS-human-intervention-policy):\\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:512:Review automation must skip PRs already labeled `human-intervention`. That\\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:514:continue, per §FS-human-intervention-policy. A PR labeled\\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:515:`human-intervention-fixed` is the explicit maintainer signal that manual\\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:521:Automated review may add or request the `human-intervention` PR label only when\\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:525:infrastructure errors must not be converted into `human-intervention` unless\\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:528:(§FS-human-intervention-policy).\\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:554:`human-intervention` for these fixable index bucket inconsistencies\\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:555:(§FS-human-intervention-policy).\\nforge/docs/functional-spec.md:572:| `SUCCESS_WITH_INTERVENTION_STATUS` | Tests succeeded after the built-in post-generation recovery modified the working tree (a Codex metadata fix, then Pi removing failing tests as a last resort), and the local CI-equivalent verification (§FS-local-ci-equivalent-verification) passed. The intervention's record is included in the run-metrics and PR description. PR-eligible; distinct from the `human-intervention` label unless §FS-human-intervention-policy separately requires that label. |\\nforge/docs/orchestration-scripts.md:149:queue label, plus PRs carrying `human-intervention-fixed`, and selects only\\nforge/docs/orchestration-scripts.md:151:not still blocked by `human-intervention`. PRs labeled `human-intervention` are\\nforge/docs/orchestration-scripts.md:152:skipped until a maintainer marks them `human-intervention-fixed`, at which point\\nforge/docs/git-scripts.md:135:references, review text, metrics summaries, and human-intervention visibility.\\nforge/docs/git-scripts.md:171:`human-intervention` and lists those paths for maintainer review\\nforge/docs/git-scripts.md:172:(§FS-human-intervention-policy).\\nforge/tests/test_forge_metadata.py:494:            forge_metadata.gh(\\\"issue\\\", \\\"edit\\\", \\\"2099\\\", \\\"--add-label\\\", \\\"human-intervention\\\")\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_24\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"I found the reason mapping in Forge. `test_generation_failed` is the workflow’s classification for generation-stage failures, and `library-preparation-preflight` has a dedicated advisory path. I’m opening those code points to verify whether this advisory result is expected to halt generation or just change inputs.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_25\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"nl -ba forge/forge_metadata.py | sed -n '3298,3325p'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_25\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"nl -ba forge/forge_metadata.py | sed -n '3298,3325p'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"  3298\\t        coverage_snapshot = None\\n  3299\\t        if isinstance(run_metrics, dict):\\n  3300\\t            strategy_name = run_metrics.get(\\\"strategy_name\\\")\\n  3301\\t            workflow_status = str(run_metrics.get(\\\"status\\\") or RUN_STATUS_FAILURE)\\n  3302\\t            coverage_snapshot = _load_dynamic_access_snapshot_from_metrics(run_metrics)\\n  3303\\t        if workflow_status in HUMAN_INTERVENTION_NON_FAILURE_STATUSES:\\n  3304\\t            return None\\n  3305\\t        if coverage_snapshot is None:\\n  3306\\t            coverage_snapshot = _load_dynamic_access_snapshot_from_report(claimed_issue)\\n  3307\\t        return HumanInterventionCandidate(\\n  3308\\t            strategy_name=strategy_name,\\n  3309\\t            workflow_status=workflow_status,\\n  3310\\t            coverage=coverage_snapshot,\\n  3311\\t            reason=\\\"test_generation_failed\\\",\\n  3312\\t        )\\n  3313\\t\\n  3314\\t    if run_metrics is None:\\n  3315\\t        return None\\n  3316\\t\\n  3317\\t    strategy_name = run_metrics.get(\\\"strategy_name\\\")\\n  3318\\t    if not strategy_name:\\n  3319\\t        return None\\n  3320\\t    if run_metrics.get(\\\"status\\\") == RUN_STATUS_CHUNK_READY:\\n  3321\\t        return None\\n  3322\\t\\n  3323\\t    strategy = load_strategy_by_name(strategy_name)\\n  3324\\t    if strategy is None or strategy.get(\\\"workflow\\\") != \\\"dynamic_access_iterative\\\":\\n  3325\\t        return None\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_26\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"nl -ba forge/utility_scripts/library_preparation_preflight.py | sed -n '630,760p'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_26\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"nl -ba forge/utility_scripts/library_preparation_preflight.py | sed -n '630,760p'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"   630\\t        reachability_repo_path: str,\\n   631\\t) -> dict[str, Any] | None:\\n   632\\t    \\\"\\\"\\\"Apply deterministic preflight setup once and idempotently, recording results.\\n   633\\t\\n   634\\t    Driver-owned step (§ORCH-forge-orchestration-spec.1.1): typed `dependency` and\\n   635\\t    `docker_image` entries are applied as source edits; unappliable entries are\\n   636\\t    left for the advisory guidance fallback. Mutates and returns the record.\\n   637\\t    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n   638\\t    if not isinstance(preflight, dict):\\n   639\\t        return preflight\\n   640\\t    if preflight.get(\\\"status\\\") != \\\"completed\\\" or preflight.get(\\\"action\\\") != \\\"advisory_preparation\\\":\\n   641\\t        preflight.setdefault(\\\"applied_setup\\\", [])\\n   642\\t        return preflight\\n   643\\t    library_coordinate = str(preflight.get(\\\"library\\\") or \\\"\\\")\\n   644\\t    applied: list[dict[str, str]] = []\\n   645\\t    for entry in preflight.get(\\\"deterministic_setup\\\") or []:\\n   646\\t        kind = entry.get(\\\"kind\\\") if isinstance(entry, dict) else None\\n   647\\t        try:\\n   648\\t            if kind == \\\"dependency\\\":\\n   649\\t                applied.append(_apply_dependency_setup(reachability_repo_path, library_coordinate, entry))\\n   650\\t            elif kind == \\\"docker_image\\\":\\n   651\\t                applied.append(_apply_docker_image_setup(reachability_repo_path, entry))\\n   652\\t        except Exception as exc:\\n   653\\t            applied.append({\\\"kind\\\": str(kind), \\\"result\\\": \\\"skipped\\\", \\\"reason\\\": f\\\"{type(exc).__name__}: {exc}\\\"})\\n   654\\t    preflight[\\\"applied_setup\\\"] = applied\\n   655\\t    return preflight\\n   656\\t\\n   657\\t\\n   658\\tdef prepare_library_preparation_preflight(\\n   659\\t        preflight_path: str | None,\\n   660\\t        reachability_repo_path: str,\\n   661\\t) -> tuple[dict[str, Any] | None, str]:\\n   662\\t    \\\"\\\"\\\"Driver entry point: load the record, apply deterministic setup, render context.\\n   663\\t\\n   664\\t    Returns the (mutated) record for metrics and the advisory-only prompt context.\\n   665\\t    Must run after the reachability repo path is resolved so source edits land in\\n   666\\t    the right worktree (§ORCH-forge-orchestration-spec.1.1).\\n   667\\t    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n   668\\t    preflight = load_library_preparation_preflight(preflight_path)\\n   669\\t    apply_library_preparation_setup(preflight, reachability_repo_path)\\n   670\\t    if isinstance(preflight, dict):\\n   671\\t        applied = preflight.get(\\\"applied_setup\\\") or []\\n   672\\t        if applied:\\n   673\\t            summary = \\\", \\\".join(\\n   674\\t                f\\\"{item.get('kind')}:{item.get('result')}\\\"\\n   675\\t                for item in applied if isinstance(item, dict)\\n   676\\t            )\\n   677\\t            log_stage(\\\"library-preflight\\\", f\\\"Applied deterministic setup: {summary}\\\")\\n   678\\t    context = format_library_preparation_preflight_context(preflight)\\n   679\\t    return preflight, context\\n   680\\t\\n   681\\t\\n   682\\tdef _format_bullets(values: list[Any]) -> str:\\n   683\\t    lines: list[str] = []\\n   684\\t    for value in values:\\n   685\\t        if isinstance(value, str) and value.strip():\\n   686\\t            lines.append(f\\\"- {value.strip()}\\\")\\n   687\\t    return \\\"\\\\n\\\".join(lines)\\n   688\\t\\n   689\\t\\n   690\\tdef _describe_setup_entry(entry: dict[str, str]) -> str:\\n   691\\t    \\\"\\\"\\\"Render one deterministic-setup entry as agent-facing fallback work.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n   692\\t    kind = entry.get(\\\"kind\\\")\\n   693\\t    if kind == \\\"dependency\\\":\\n   694\\t        return f\\\"Add {entry.get('scope', 'testImplementation')} dependency {entry.get('coordinate')}\\\"\\n   695\\t    if kind == \\\"docker_image\\\":\\n   696\\t        return f\\\"Use Docker image {entry.get('image')} (allow-list slug {entry.get('slug')})\\\"\\n   697\\t    return str(entry)\\n   698\\t\\n   699\\t\\n   700\\tdef _applied_setup_descriptions(preflight: dict[str, Any]) -> list[str]:\\n   701\\t    \\\"\\\"\\\"Describe deterministic setup already applied or already present.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n   702\\t    setup_by_key: dict[tuple[Any, Any], dict[str, str]] = {}\\n   703\\t    for entry in preflight.get(\\\"deterministic_setup\\\") or []:\\n   704\\t        if isinstance(entry, dict):\\n   705\\t            setup_by_key[(entry.get(\\\"kind\\\"), entry.get(\\\"coordinate\\\") or entry.get(\\\"slug\\\"))] = entry\\n   706\\t\\n   707\\t    descriptions: list[str] = []\\n   708\\t    for item in preflight.get(\\\"applied_setup\\\") or []:\\n   709\\t        if not isinstance(item, dict) or item.get(\\\"result\\\") not in {\\\"applied\\\", \\\"already_present\\\"}:\\n   710\\t            continue\\n   711\\t        key = (item.get(\\\"kind\\\"), item.get(\\\"coordinate\\\") or item.get(\\\"slug\\\"))\\n   712\\t        entry = setup_by_key.get(key, item)\\n   713\\t        state = \\\"already present\\\" if item.get(\\\"result\\\") == \\\"already_present\\\" else \\\"applied\\\"\\n   714\\t        descriptions.append(f\\\"{_describe_setup_entry(entry)} ({state})\\\")\\n   715\\t    return descriptions\\n   716\\t\\n   717\\t\\n   718\\tdef _pending_setup_descriptions(preflight: dict[str, Any]) -> list[str]:\\n   719\\t    \\\"\\\"\\\"Describe deterministic entries the driver did not apply, for agent fallback.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n   720\\t    results: dict[tuple[Any, Any], Any] = {}\\n   721\\t    for item in preflight.get(\\\"applied_setup\\\") or []:\\n   722\\t        if isinstance(item, dict):\\n   723\\t            results[(item.get(\\\"kind\\\"), item.get(\\\"coordinate\\\") or item.get(\\\"slug\\\"))] = item.get(\\\"result\\\")\\n   724\\t    descriptions: list[str] = []\\n   725\\t    for entry in preflight.get(\\\"deterministic_setup\\\") or []:\\n   726\\t        if not isinstance(entry, dict):\\n   727\\t            continue\\n   728\\t        key = (entry.get(\\\"kind\\\"), entry.get(\\\"coordinate\\\") or entry.get(\\\"slug\\\"))\\n   729\\t        if results.get(key) in {\\\"applied\\\", \\\"already_present\\\"}:\\n   730\\t            continue\\n   731\\t        descriptions.append(_describe_setup_entry(entry))\\n   732\\t    return descriptions\\n   733\\t\\n   734\\t\\n   735\\tdef format_library_preparation_preflight_context(preflight: dict[str, Any] | None) -> str:\\n   736\\t    \\\"\\\"\\\"Render preflight summary, applied setup, and guidance for workflow prompts.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n   737\\t    if not isinstance(preflight, dict):\\n   738\\t        return NO_LIBRARY_PREPARATION_PREFLIGHT_CONTEXT\\n   739\\t\\n   740\\t    action = str(preflight.get(\\\"action\\\") or \\\"no_action\\\")\\n   741\\t    summary = str(preflight.get(\\\"summary\\\") or \\\"\\\").strip()\\n   742\\t    if action != \\\"advisory_preparation\\\":\\n   743\\t        reason = str(preflight.get(\\\"failure_reason\\\") or \\\"\\\").strip()\\n   744\\t        if reason:\\n   745\\t            return f\\\"{NO_LIBRARY_PREPARATION_PREFLIGHT_CONTEXT} Reason: {reason}\\\"\\n   746\\t        if summary:\\n   747\\t            return f\\\"{NO_LIBRARY_PREPARATION_PREFLIGHT_CONTEXT} Summary: {summary}\\\"\\n   748\\t        return NO_LIBRARY_PREPARATION_PREFLIGHT_CONTEXT\\n   749\\t\\n   750\\t    guidance = str(preflight.get(\\\"agent_guidance\\\") or \\\"\\\").strip()\\n   751\\t    applied_setup = _format_bullets(_applied_setup_descriptions(preflight))\\n   752\\t    pending_setup = _format_bullets(_pending_setup_descriptions(preflight))\\n   753\\t    risks = _format_bullets(preflight.get(\\\"risks\\\") or [])\\n   754\\t\\n   755\\t    sections = [\\\"Library preparation preflight produced setup context.\\\"]\\n   756\\t    if summary:\\n   757\\t        sections.extend([\\\"\\\", f\\\"Summary: {summary}\\\"])\\n   758\\t    if applied_setup:\\n   759\\t        sections.extend([\\\"\\\", \\\"Already applied by Forge:\\\", applied_setup])\\n   760\\t    if guidance:\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_27\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"nl -ba forge/docs/functional-spec.md | sed -n '371,410p'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"\",\"exit_code\":null,\"status\":\"in_progress\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_27\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"nl -ba forge/docs/functional-spec.md | sed -n '371,410p'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"   371\\t### FS-human-intervention-policy: Human intervention policy\\n   372\\t\\n   373\\tThe `human-intervention` label is a maintainer follow-up signal, not a generic\\n   374\\tfailure label. Forge must apply it only when the available evidence shows that\\n   375\\tthe work cannot be safely completed or trusted without human judgment about the\\n   376\\tgenerated code, repository automation, metadata, or library behavior.\\n   377\\t\\n   378\\tValid human-intervention cases are semantic or generation failures inside\\n   379\\tForge's responsibility boundary, including:\\n   380\\t\\n   381\\t- Generated tests, metadata, or workflow edits fail local verification in a way\\n   382\\t  that points to the generated artifact or repository automation rather than a\\n   383\\t  transient external service.\\n   384\\t- The workflow cannot converge after its configured generation, retry, and\\n   385\\t  recovery limits, and the saved logs point to a real library/test/metadata\\n   386\\t  problem that needs maintainer analysis.\\n   387\\t- Dynamic-access coverage remains missing or suspiciously low after a\\n   388\\t  successful generation path, making the result misleading without manual\\n   389\\t  follow-up.\\n   390\\t- Local CI-equivalent verification passes only after shared repository files\\n   391\\t  changed, so a maintainer must review repository-level effects before merge.\\n   392\\t- Publication detects a severe metadata, test, or coverage anomaly that makes\\n   393\\t  the PR unsafe to auto-review as a normal generated result.\\n   394\\t\\n   395\\tForge must not use `human-intervention` for failures that are only external or\\n   396\\ttransient infrastructure conditions. The issue-side classification is by failure\\n   397\\torigin, not by log keywords: a workflow failure is **logical** — and gets the\\n   398\\tlabel — when it comes from the driver script, the core workflow, or the local\\n   399\\tCI-equivalent verification (compile, test, native-test, and finalization gates),\\n   400\\twhich includes the rare case of an agent timeout. A workflow failure is\\n   401\\t**external** — and must not get the label — only when it surfaces as a typed\\n   402\\texception from the dependency boundary Forge itself crosses: GitHub (`gh`: rate\\n   403\\tlimits and 5xx/network) as `GitHubError` / `GitHubRateLimitExceeded`, and remote\\n   404\\tgit operations (push/pull/fetch/clone/ls-remote) as `GitTransportError`. Maven\\n   405\\tCentral and Docker registry failures have no such boundary — Gradle owns them\\n   406\\tinside `./gradlew test` and they reach Forge only as an opaque CI-check `rc != 0`,\\n   407\\tindistinguishable from a real test failure once the in-workflow retries have run —\\n   408\\tso they are not special-cased and fall through to the safe logical default. When a\\n   409\\tfailure is external, Forge takes no issue action: it applies no\\n   410\\t`human-intervention` label and posts no comment, and silently releases the issue\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_28\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"I want one more check on the preserved branch ancestry. If there’s an earlier `add-lib-support` branch with actual generated artifacts, that changes the diagnosis; if not, then this really died before